OL,3,CWhat is pre-diabetes and how can it be
OL,4,Ctreated?
OL,6,F"If your blood glucose levels, which
OL,7,Fare not controlled correctly, affects
OL,8,Fyour big blood vessels, then you're at
OL,9,Frisk of a heart attack, stroke, or
OL,10,Faffecting your circulation - which is
OL,11,Fcalled peripheral vascular disease.
OL,13,F"These can increase the risk of you
OL,14,Fbecoming unwell and even increase the
OL,15,Fchances of death."
OL,17,FWhat is non-diabetic hyperglycaemia or
OL,18,Fpre-diabetes?
