OL,3,CWhat is pre-diabetes and how can it be
OL,4,Ctreated?
OL,6,FIn Sussex, 197,000 people, which is
OL,7,Faround 10% of the population, are
OL,8,Fliving with non-diabetic
OL,9,Fhyperglycaemia, also known as pre-
OL,10,Fdiabetes.
OL,12,FIt means their blood sugar levels are
OL,13,Fabove the normal range, but not high
OL,14,Fenough to be diagnosed with diabetes.
OL,16,FIt also means they are at higher risk
OL,17,Fof developing Type 2 diabetes, which
OL,18,Fcan cause loss of vision or kidney
OL,19,Fproblems, as well as other even more
OL,20,Fcomplex health issues.
